The Role:

Entegris is seeking a Scientist to accelerate the development of next generation of chemical mechanical polishing processes for next generation of emerging materials such as carbides, nitrides, metals and dielectrics. The job will entail development of new engineered particles, modification of particle surfaces and novel additive chemistries that enhance polishing of such materials. This position is located in Gainesville, Florida.

In this role you will:
Lead Scientist for the synthesis and surface modification of particles and formulation of slurries;
Provide guidance while promoting teamwork within the R&D team;
Improve laboratory infrastructure for development and characterization of CMP processes;
Develop relationships with key personnel at Entegris’ customers,
Coordinate interactions with cross-functional teams such as Analytical, development teams, Operations, Marketing and Sales,
Represent Entegris at technical conferences,
Develop innovative technology and create intellectual property on new products and ideas;
Maintain a safe working environment.
