Ph.D. in engineering, material science or chemistry with experience in particle or surface science;
Experience in the semiconductor industry, developing technology, preferably in CMP;
Project management experience, with a track record of planning, driving and executing projects;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills, with an ability to develop and present technical materials to internal and external customers;
Innovative in nature and ability to execute on new ideas;
Ability to design and conduct experiments;
Data analysis and excellent deductive skills;
Experience transitioning research into patents and products;
Collaborative approach to working within a team environment.
Your success will be measured by:
Technical contributions in slurry development;
Transitioning R&D into patents and products;
Working collaboratively with team members.
